cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with semi-supervised image classification using graph networks and prototype generation. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a novel architecture for semi-supervised learning. The paper also deals with computer vision (cs.CV) as it focuses on image classification. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new method for learning from unlabeled data. The paper also deals with natural language processing (cs.CL) as it uses graph networks for feature propagation. Finally, the paper involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it proposes an end-to-end architecture for semi-supervised learning.
